OL,3,CFake cancer charity worker stole
OL,4,C#18,000 from vulnerable men
OL,6,FRedmond once again tried to attend the
OL,7,Fvictim's address within days of being
OL,8,Freleased from prison in February 2024.
OL,10,FTwo months later, a second person
OL,11,Freported that Redmond had been
OL,12,Fvisiting his home requesting money,
OL,13,Fagain fraudulently acting as a charity
OL,14,Fcollector.
OL,16,FThe elderly victim was told to
OL,17,Fwithdraw cash from his bank account
OL,18,Fseveral times during the day and night
OL,19,Fover a period of a month, until
OL,20,Feventually he gave Redmond over #8,000.
