OL,6,FRedmond was sentenced to four and a
OL,7,Fhalf years in prison for two counts of
OL,8,Ffraud by false representation.
OL,9,FIndefinite restraining orders have
OL,10,Fbeen put in place to protect both
OL,11,Fvictims.
OL,13,FDetective Constable Alexandra Lindley
OL,14,Fsaid: "Targeting vulnerable people in
OL,15,Ftheir own homes and scamming them out
OL,16,Fof their savings is truly unacceptable.
OL,18,F"Redmond took advantage of the two
OL,19,Fvictims who believed they were helping
OL,20,Fa charitable cause, when in fact they
OL,21,Fwere feeding Redmond's greed.
